 players then also can say this is the way we want it done on our server any who petition would  then have to go to a gm and tell them they want this camp to themselves while we as players say no we will allow you your fair turn of looting if you join in with us and help to kill the mob. At this point we are displaying the exact idea that the play nice policy asks and the GM's would have no choice but to side with us and say to the petitioner you can join by there rules or leave. So its all a matter of people if we can find say 15 guilds who will support this and can supply 2 balanced 50-54 groups we are talking about 30 groups scheduled to watch the spawn and camp until we feel we have satisfied our needs. Also people will say well some guilds after they get theres will just leave the aggreement and not send groups anymore, well no maybe they will leave but after we have controlled the spawn long enough it will become a custom that we as players will have to continue to make sure it is obeyed this way a guild wanting this item has no choice but to join and obey the play nice policy we are just trying to actually enforce. In my opinion we could start a trend that if followed to the letter verant may even decide to support and develop the standpoint of support to such organizations. Maybe we make the fire giants ,naggy ragefire into a point based loot system all people who spend time at the camp gain points which will be used to purchase the loot that comes form this camp and it is pretty profitable with RF's loot and Naggy so we elevate the values somewhat because more people will be spending time there and we know everyone will get themselves an item at some point to help repay there dedication.            <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 So obviously this is a rough idea but with though and the willingness to try and make it work we can turn this situation around. We wont have to see any guild feel hostility to anyone else because the got beat to this spawn for the umpteenth time because there were a little late.<br>
<br>
<br>
